---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout title="Our Journey | Samantha Ritter & Daniel Brykalov">
  <section class="journey-page">
    <div class="journey-hero">
      <div class="journey-hero-text">
        <p class="eyebrow">OUR JOURNEY</p>
        <h1>Two Paths. One Dream.</h1>
        <p>
          Before becoming an international ice dance team, Samantha Ritter and
          Daniel Brykalov spent years training side by side as friends — sharing
          the same ice, the same dedication, and the same dream of reaching the
          highest level of the sport.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-image-card">
        <img src="/images/journey-hero.jpg" alt="Samantha Ritter and Daniel Brykalov" />
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="timeline">
      <article class="timeline-card">
        <span class="year">2018</span>
        <h2>The Beginning</h2>
        <p>
          Samantha and Daniel first met in Novi, Michigan in 2018 while training
          under renowned coach Igor Shpilband. Although they skated with
          different partners at the time, they quickly developed a strong
          friendship built through countless hours of training and shared
          experiences on and off the ice.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="timeline-card">
        <span class="year">2021</span>
        <h2>A New Partnership</h2>
        <p>
          After years of training alongside each other, Samantha and Daniel made
          a decision that would change the course of their careers. In January
          2021, they officially joined forces as an ice dance team.
        </p>
        <p>
          Their friendship had already created a strong foundation of trust,
          commitment, and belief in what they could achieve together.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="timeline-card canada-card">
        <span class="year">2021–2026</span>
        <h2>A New Home in Canada</h2>
        <p>
          Shortly after forming their partnership, Samantha and Daniel relocated
          to London, Ontario, Canada, to continue pursuing their goals at the
          highest level of international ice dance.
        </p>
        <p>
          There, they trained at the Ice Academy of Montreal's London Campus
          under the guidance of Olympic Champion and ice dance legend Scott Moir,
          whose experience and leadership helped shape the next stage of their
          development as athletes.
        </p>
        <p>
          Their years in Canada became a defining chapter of their career.
          Working within one of the world's most respected training environments,
          Samantha and Daniel refined their technical skills, strengthened their
          partnership, and gained invaluable international experience.
        </p>
        <p>
          Under Scott Moir's guidance, they achieved one of their most important
          milestones, earning qualification to the World Championships on two
          separate occasions and continuing to establish themselves on the
          international stage.
        </p>

        <div class="achievement-strip">
          <div>
            <strong>Olympic Champion Guidance</strong>
            <span>Training under Scott Moir</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong>Two World Qualifications</strong>
            <span>Representing Azerbaijan internationally</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong>Elite Training Environment</strong>
            <span>Ice Academy of Montreal — London Campus</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p>
          Samantha and Daniel remain deeply grateful to Scott Moir, the coaching
          staff, and everyone who supported their development during this
          important period of their journey.
        </p>

        <div class="photo-pair">
          <img src="/images/canada-worlds-1.jpg" alt="Samantha and Daniel at an international competition" />
          <img src="/images/canada-worlds-2.jpg" alt="Samantha and Daniel performing on the world stage" />
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="timeline-card flag-card">
        <span class="year">Azerbaijan</span>
        <h2>Representing Azerbaijan</h2>

        <p class="flag-intro">
          <strong>International pride. National responsibility.</strong>
        </p>

        <p>
          Representing Azerbaijan is a source of tremendous pride and
          responsibility for Samantha and Daniel.
        </p>
        <p>
          Every competition is an opportunity to showcase not only their athletic
          abilities, but also the passion, artistry, and dedication that define
          the sport of ice dance.
        </p>
        <p>
          As they continue their journey, Samantha and Daniel remain committed to
          representing Azerbaijan with professionalism, integrity, and excellence
          on the international stage.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="timeline-card highlight">
        <span class="year">2026 — New Jersey</span>
        <h2>A New Chapter</h2>
        <p>
          In the summer of 2026, Samantha and Daniel embraced the next step in
          their competitive journey. After several successful seasons in Canada,
          they relocated to New Jersey to join a new coaching team led by
          Olympian Igor Lukanin.
        </p>
        <p>
          As a former Olympic athlete and international competitor who proudly
          represented Azerbaijan, Igor brings a unique perspective and firsthand
          understanding of the path Samantha and Daniel are pursuing.
        </p>
        <p>
          Beginning July 1, 2026, Samantha and Daniel start this new chapter
          with renewed motivation, fresh energy, and a clear vision for the
          future.
        </p>
        <p>
          While they will always value the lessons and achievements that shaped
          their years in Canada, they are equally excited about the opportunities
          ahead and look forward to working with their new coaching team as they
          continue representing Azerbaijan on the international stage.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="timeline-card final-card">
        <span class="year">Future</span>
        <h2>Building Toward the Future</h2>
        <p>
          Their story is still being written. With every competition, every
          performance, and every season on the ice, Samantha and Daniel continue
          pursuing excellence and pushing the boundaries of what they can
          achieve together.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style is:global>
  .journey-page {
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding: 9rem 1rem 5rem;
    background:
      linear-gradient(
        180deg,
        rgba(3, 10, 22, 0.94) 0%,
        rgba(10, 28, 52, 0.96) 45%,
        rgba(5, 12, 24, 1) 100%
      ),
      url("/images/hero-bg.png");
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center top;
    color: white;
  }

  .journey-hero {
    width: min(100%, 1180px);
    margin: 0 auto 5rem;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.15fr 0.85fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .journey-hero .eyebrow,
  .year {
    color: #f3d46b;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.28em;
    font-weight: 900;
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .journey-hero h1 {
    white-space: nowrap;
    font-size: clamp(3.2rem, 4.8vw, 5.2rem);
    line-height: 0.95;
    letter-spacing: -0.05em;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #fff8d8 0%, #ffe27a 45%, #d6a832 100%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    text-shadow:
      0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.25),
      0 3px 0 rgba(122,86,10,0.35),
      0 8px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.26);
  }

  .journey-hero p {
    max-width: 760px;
    font-size: 1.22rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.86);
  }

  .hero-image-card,
  .photo-pair img {
    overflow: hidden;
    border-radius: 28px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.14);
    box-shadow: 0 24px 60px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
  }

  .hero-image-card {
    aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
  }

  .hero-image-card img,
  .photo-pair img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    display: block;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .timeline {
    width: min(100%, 1080px);
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.7rem;
  }

  .timeline-card {
    position: relative;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 28px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.075);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.13);
    box-shadow: 0 24px 60px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25);
    backdrop-filter: blur(14px);
  }

  .timeline-card.highlight,
  .timeline-card.final-card {
    border-color: rgba(243, 212, 107, 0.45);
    box-shadow:
      0 24px 60px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.28),
      0 0 34px rgba(243, 212, 107, 0.12);
  }

  .flag-card {
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    border-color: rgba(243, 212, 107, 0.32);
  }

 .flag-card::before {
  content: "";
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;

  background:
    linear-gradient(
      180deg,
      rgba(0,168,225,.28) 0%,
      rgba(0,168,225,.28) 33%,
      rgba(237,41,57,.24) 33%,
      rgba(237,41,57,.24) 66%,
      rgba(0,146,70,.26) 66%,
      rgba(0,146,70,.26) 100%
    );

  z-index: 0;
}

.flag-card::after {
  content: "";
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;

  background:
    linear-gradient(
      135deg,
      rgba(8,14,26,.62),
      rgba(18,28,46,.42)
    );

  z-index: 1;
}

  .flag-card > * {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
  }

  .timeline-card h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.7rem, 3vw, 2.6rem);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: #fff2b5;
  }

  .timeline-card p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.82);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .timeline-card p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .achievement-strip {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .achievement-strip div {
    padding: 1.15rem;
    border-radius: 20px;
    background: rgba(243, 212, 107, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(243, 212, 107, 0.22);
  }

  .achievement-strip strong {
    display: block;
    color: #fff2b5;
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .achievement-strip span {
    display: block;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.72);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
  }

  .photo-pair {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .photo-pair img {
    aspect-ratio: 4 / 3;
  }

  @media (min-width: 900px) {
    .timeline-card {
      width: 82%;
    }

    .timeline-card:nth-child(even) {
      margin-left: auto;
    }

    .canada-card,
    .flag-card {
      width: 100%;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .journey-hero {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .journey-hero h1 {
      white-space: normal;
    }

    .achievement-strip {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .journey-page {
      padding-top: 8rem;
    }

    .journey-hero {
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .journey-hero p,
    .timeline-card p {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .timeline-card {
      padding: 1.5rem;
      border-radius: 22px;
    }

    .photo-pair {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>